Sales And Marketing Director - PT Easypay Indonesia
Sales And Marketing Director  -
Sales And Marketing Director
Responsibilities
MaleAge 30 - 40 years oldMain Location: JakartaCandidate must possess at least a DiplomaSkills-Qualifications: Meeting Sales Goals, Negotiation, Sales Planning, Building Relationships, Market KnowledgeCompensation: IDR 15.000.000 plusIncentive Bonuses: Provided as per execution of sales and marketing plan (minimum as 13th Salary)Job Duties:Planning:Determining sales strategy both annual and by month by implementing marketing strategies; analyzing trends and results. (usage of economics skills is welcomed)Establishing sales objectives by forecasting and developing monthly sales quotas for regions and territories; projecting expected sales volume for existing and new products.Research and development of partners network for market penetration.Execution:Coordinating the specific objectives of the Sales Plan with all of the functional departments of the company and, most specifically with Chief Business Development Officer, establish both market and target customer/ partner strategies for the Company.Establishing and maintaining partnership relations with Food Retail Businesses. (Existing knowledge of the Market will be considered as a plus)Developing strong presence of the Company on the Market by representing it on exhibitions, trade shows, conferences and etc.Maintaining balance between sales volume, product mix and revenue margins by keeping current with supply and demand, changing trends, economic indicators, and competitors.Establishing and adjusting selling prices by monitoring costs, competition and supply and demand.Maintaining professional and technical knowledge by reviewing professional publications; establishing personal networks; participating in professional societies.Keep up to date with recent market and industry trends, competitors, and leading customer strategies.Contributing to team effort by accomplishing related results as needed.The position specifically is responsible for B2B (business to business) sales via direct market penetration, co-networking and telemarketing, as well as all business sales and development functions of the Company.A significant portion of time Sales and Marketing Director would be engaged in the field both on individual accounts and with other Company employees.
